A buck converter is a DC-DC converter that steps down an input voltage to a lower output voltage.

For an ideal buck converter:

Vout = D × Vin

where:

- Vout = Output Voltage
- Vin = Input Voltage
- D = Duty Cycle

| Output | Duty Cycle |
| ------ | ---------- |
| 3.3V   | ~23%       |
| 5V     | ~42%       |
| 9V     | ~75%       |
